##The "little Hong Kong" under the epidemic situation is still the single-reading of that small county town

Its content is mainly fiction, poetry, cultural criticism, ideological essays, non-fiction reports and works of art, respect quiet, deep, elegant reading, respect sober, unique, dynamic voice, committed to become a source of ideas for young people around the world.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"New crown" pneumonia like a knife, not only hurt the flesh and blood, but also cut into the bone marrow of the lesion. The sober man must speak his voice and speak his truth. The writer of today's letter is Wu Junyu from Yichun, Jiangxi Province. In the past period, with the rapid development of the national economy, Yichun has also created a prosperous scene. Unexpectedly, the outbreak came, the town as if back to the original.

"Little Hong Kong" under epidemic situation, return that small county eventually

By Oh joon-woo

Go

What is happiness? What is life? What is value? I searched for answers in Alain Badiou's what it is to live and George Levan's the pleasures of secularism.

It wasn't easy for me until a few years ago. I wake up at 6 am, flustered and hungry, to write for the Internet companies. I spent a week in the morning on "excellent daily food" -- as if I had spent it on Pumpkin Gruel, mustard-leaf Buns, date and soy milk, and Japanese strawberries.

To others, I looked free and comfortable. Stay at home all day, tired of stroking the cat, in the various enterprises, the city's activities shuttle back and forth. But the market for authors has been purged wave after wave, and those group visits haven't really penetrated the business itself, producing content that has limited value. The industry forces you to move forward, and you can only learn and sell quickly. The crisis is deep. Unable to extricate themselves emotionally, can only run to the community, while listening to Xu Zhiyuan's "thirteen nights" , while walking around a circle. This state of life is, in fact, the daily equivalent of our circle: anxiety, anxiety, anxiety, unceasing anxiety.

I saw a media entrepreneur lying in his office all night. She said she was 27,28 years old, this is a little girl, other people are playing around, but she has to shoulder the pressure. Her real dream is to take her children to study in America. Another media entrepreneur lost all her hair at the beginning of the year. Ask just know, he says he is the boss of more than a dozen people, in fact, is to work for the staff, the sense of happiness is very poor. He wants to go back to being alone. A friend said he was pinching his nose at the "Greasy Bureau" to dress up and party for a year of networking. His real dream life was to travel and document the lives of others. He wanted to live like this after he turned 40.

I am reminded of the "Work Hole" theory of anthropologist Xiang Biao. He used it to illustrate the futility of pursuing my passion for success, as if what I do today is really of little value, or what I really want to do. But I'm GonNa do this and that. I'm just GONNA bite the bullet here, and then I'm GonNa come back and I'm gonNA live. Well, since I'm the closest to the fire, I might as well get my money's worth and jump in.

However, Xiang Biao directly pointed out that this "after a good life" is a self-deception lies. Yeah, well, it's hard to live in the present, let alone the future. One time I was talking to the driver of a Didi special bus. He was a middle-aged man with straight hair and a black thermal jacket. He said he made $20 million by contracting government projects. Thirty years later, he was a mediocre and UNAMBITIOUS, drinking and singing every day, and didn't care for his children. You drink hard, you sing hard, you make money hard. Time flies. Ten years is like two or three. I can still see the days before thirty, just yesterday. At 40, I just want to drive a special car and have a good rest. His son is in trouble. He wants to be sent to a government institution. He spent the rest of his life with twenty million in his arms, his face tired and his passion gone.

If he's GonNa live another 40 years, that $20 million is GONNA cost him $500,000 a year. This is also the case that investment does not fail, the body does not collapse, and inflation does not occur. It doesn't make any sense, really, to have it all figured out. I seemed to see in him the helplessness one might have in middle age.

Small Year that day, I put a few friends who have no utilitarian heart together, together in the Beijing Hutong of the Japanese material shop to chat a night. "It's like climbing out of a flooded well, " another friend, who has been deeply involved in complicated relationships at work, told me on wechat after the meal. I felt the warmth and the reward of receiving the message. "Happiness" , "life" and "value" are ultimately built up in relationships and the smell of daily bread and salt, rather than a person living apart from his family and working frantically for money, or sacrifice your family for your so-called dreams. Those so-called "ambitions" , "achievements" , it brings a sense of value is actually far less than a family sitting peacefully together for dinner, even lower than the more humane choice, as if, after all, human nature is the manifestation of divinity, it is the fruit of compassion.

I feel like I'm getting a little piece of the answer.

Down

On the day I returned to the small town in the south, I found an advertisement for an airport in my hometown. It read three paragraphs: Top 100 counties and cities in China in terms of overall strength; top 100 counties and cities in China in terms of happiness; and top 100 counties and cities in China in terms of investment potential. I scoff a bit, especially since the word "happiness" makes me deeply suspicious. This suspicion stems from a rebellion against home.

But walking with my mother at night, I realized I was wrong. After a year without going home, I became a tourist attraction. The centre of Laocheng District was transformed into the "three palaces" , named after the "three palaces" -- a temple built in the 13th year of the reign of Emperor Guangxu in 1887 but ignored by the local people for many years.

The city's commercial center has quietly shifted. In the 1990s, "little Hong Kong" has been aging, falling apart, once the Shanzhai foreign brands have closed. The Old City has been transformed into the "Sanhuangli" business district, which is a cluster of antique buildings, filled with young people, full of Hanfu shops. Back around 2010, the town also had a business center called Manhattan. All three business centers are within a kilometer of each other. From "little Hong Kong" to "Manhattan" to "three kings lane" , the flow of people, every kilometer is the new era of the old era of correction and reverse.

"San Huang Li" business district at the door of the "Internet Celebrity Food Festival. Here gathered in Beijing, Tianjin, Chongqing, Sichuan, Hunan, Inner Mongolia, Hong Kong and other places "characteristics of snacks. ". Commercial Area Interior then built each kind of shop according to the standard "scenic spot pattern" . Among them are made in Yiwu and cook in Jiangxi. The streets were festooned with lights and people coming and going, and the joy of returning home for the Spring Festival was on people's faces. There were even elderly people taking street photographs in the business district.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I don't want to evaluate the so-called "Internet Celebrity Food Festival" from a sociological point of view, nor do I want to dwell on what kind of social trends mean by changing the name of the city's business center. From the perspective of ordinary life, a small town suddenly takes on the appearance of a small city. This peaceful atmosphere was last seen in Taipei and Chengdu. At first glance, home does suddenly have a few minutes Taipei, Chengdu's Leisure Happiness. However, my mother and I chat while walking, worried about this wave of Spring Festival home rush, it will not hold up. Because shadows are shadows, and they lack the support of real life. After all, cities aren't made of buildings, they're made of people.

My suspicions were confirmed, or worse. The Black Swan has arrived. It's an epidemic.

On the third day of the first lunar month, I went out and found that all the shops in "little Hong Kong" and "three kings lane" were closed. Before the outbreak of the image of one after another has been replaced by the present empty.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
And in previous years, "little Hong Kong" is the most prosperous place in the city, the young people back home in the milk tea shop, coffee shop, chatting, playing cards. The "three kings lane" also has a crowded music tavern years ago, but now close the door. Two notices were posted at the door, one on big red paper reading "follow the human-oriented management philosophy... give all staff a holiday during the Spring Festival... regular work on the third day" , and the following was signed "music pub for the relief of sorrow" . The other is an "emergency notice" on epidemic prevention and control. "from January 26(the second day of the first lunar month) , all business will be suspended, no parties and banquets will be held, and the opening time will be announced separately, " the A4 white paper said, signed with the official seal of the market supervision administration and the ice-cold seal.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Red And white paper is a thin line. It's absurd. I wonder if the owner of this pub needs to drink at home during the Spring Festival.

I can't imagine the anxiety the families behind those stores are experiencing. They may be saving up to buy their next one hundred thousand, hoping to cash in on the Spring Festival rush to return home, but their hopes have been dashed. This is a disaster for offline brick and mortar stores. All walks of life stopped, leaving only supermarkets, convenience stores are still barely open. I've been thinking about how much retail sales of consumer goods will fall in the first quarter.

Internet companies in the Spring Festival speed is still extremely fast, large companies can rely on their own resources and efficiency to do some public welfare to epidemic areas, some small and medium-sized companies are not to be outdone, began to "dry hot spot" , dry after is to find the media to do dissemination. I remain detached and alert to the spread. It seems to be some kind of upward reporting, as if for public good, but far from the epidemic itself. This kind of behavior also lets a part of employee antipathy, caused crisis on the public opinion field, public relations department has to pinch nose to delete a post again.

A group of companies in doing public welfare at the same time began to push business, pull traffic. In the words of a friend, this is a "much more cost-effective than advertising" business opportunity, then the competition is to run, retain, conversion capacity. Start-up media are scrambling for hot topics, ranging from the impact of the epidemic on the macro-economy, specific industries and companies, to business stories, character stories and opinion reviews. This is probably Luo Zhenyu often said the "small trend" and "bow into the game.

"programmers, product managers, operations and markets, as well as customer service, couriers, deliverymen, and ride-hailing drivers, all have different responsibilities, but all are working for the same victory, " wrote Shen Xiang, an Internet start-up media outlet, in "996" on the Chinese Internet in the midst of a pneumonia epidemic, victory. The Spring Festival is supposed to be a time of joy for the whole family, and the onset of the epidemic is supposed to be a time of rest and recuperation. At this point to see some enterprises but in order to "victory" under the guise of disaster relief to full power, like moving forward.

A passive "996" friend told me that in this case, the company employees were kidnapped. She wanted to allow both people to participate in overtime with or without money or naive ideas, and people to refuse overtime with a fear of death or laziness. This Spring Festival, she originally intended to rest, but once again because right and wrong, and many other issues into anxiety.

Maybe it's my laziness and boredom. I don't want to catch so-called "small trends" , let alone "dive in" . I completely rejected all enterprises Spring Festival marketing and epidemic marketing of the draft. Not because I'm so noble, but because I haven't been home in a year, and I want to spend the holidays with my parents. After all, a few months ago, my mother was recovering from depression. I, who was also depressed at the time, knew how helpless it felt. I was in Beijing at the time and there was nothing I could do on the other end. All I can do now is spend more time with her on vacation.

During the outbreak, the family was locked up together. The "forced intimacy" between the two generations has caused a lot of friction. These stumbles are life itself.

Before the Spring Festival, parents were initially unaware of the outbreak. Father once extremely arrogant said, "SARS still did not panic, a righteous fear of the virus. ". I suggested cancelling this year's Spring Festival dinner, New Year activities, the result was taught "excessive panic, no family. ". I was silent. Choose to relay People's Daily, CCTV news and Zhong Nanshan's exhortations intermittently. It was only with the deluge of more than a dozen wechat messages that he began to realize the seriousness of the problem.

The barriers to communication between the two generations are on full display in the outbreak. He seems to place more trust in authority and experience than in the judgment of the next generation. After all, being pushed around by the next generation on big family issues means you're really getting old.

He probably still wants to maintain his authority over me. It's a father's authority over his son. However, the strength of the two generations, he can not control my life path, only in those minor details on the "force too much. ". For example, when should I go back to Beijing when the epidemic is in doubt. I had a huge argument with him on this issue, and during the altercation I said "no communication. " He was silent. At that moment, I kind of regretted saying something like that. Because I knew that his unquestioned tone was his way of showing his love.

After a lunch break, my mother laughed when I told her a joke. She said I was happy you were home, and if you weren't here this time, watching the news about the epidemic, I'd be depressed again. I knew my mother to be kind and gentle. When the Wenchuan County earthquake struck, she was always moved by the sad news and was always in a heavy mood. As soon as she said that, I decided to change my flight to Beijing. Love requires the art of expression, and emotional expression is far warmer than rational calculation. And that's the part I need to keep learning.

While I was at home, my mother and I kept the news of the outbreak to ourselves. They watch the new matchmaking conference every night on Jiangsu Satellite TV, where two generations sit together to exchange ideas about marriage and love. It was a rare experience in the past. In this traditional Conservative family, we are always ashamed to express, many things to the point.

I like the passage in the thank you chapter of "the pleasures of secularism" : "He turns every time he eats ice cream and every walk into a serious and productive discussion. " I envy people who mix knowledge and practice well in their daily walks, meals and conversations, they also yearn for things that are warm, precise, and cajoling. These moments of everyday life are the secular pleasures of the epidemic.

These days I turn to Peter Watson's history of Twentieth Century Thought: From Floyd to the Internet. In many German speaking countries, scientists and pseudo scientists, philosophers and pseudo philosophers, intellectuals and pseudo intellectuals all try to outdo each other in the battle for public attention, the book says.

The same is true of the public-opinion game in this epidemic. Every day on social media sounds like a concerto. The large strings hummed like rain, The small strings whispered like a secret,. Each statement represents a trend of thought. Trends and trends are intertwined, and the forces of these trends change with the changing reality, and together they create a basic social media consensus. We are judging, we are moving, we are angry, we are laughing, we seem to be participating in an orgy, seems to be away from the real world.

I remembered a passage I wrote a year ago: "every age has its drunkenness, its cowardice, its discontent and its sneers. ". The Soviets are in the kitchen, the white-collar Americans are in the bar, and the Chinese are probably on social media."

We think we're changing something, but we're not changing anything. Life is always going according to its logic. Whether the outbreak exists or not.

I caught it on my phone with a Telephoto Lens on my balcony during a boring day. This is the "Sanhuangli" a street outside a piece of green dust covered by the ruins. Under the ruins lay the streets and factories of the town for decades. Above the ruins are isolated trees, carelessly dumped household waste, and a vegetable garden ringed with broken bricks by nearby residents.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A group of desperate gamblers on the sunny fifth day moved out of the card table, in the ruins of the crowd gambling. Next to them were old people, children and puppies. They were the only sights I could see.

If there's no outbreak, they're still gambling, just not wearing masks. That's all. A small town is a small town. Even if the empty shell of some parts of Chengdu, Taipei, civilization is still far beyond reach. The ruins, and the spiritual life of the people on them, are the foundation of the town.

February 1, Yichun, Jiangxi

Since the essay, we have received a large number of submissions, writing truthfully about what they saw and heard during the epidemic. It will be a sincere and weighty record, and we will keep it.
